##### Information and Coding Theory

*   Main articles: [Information theory](/Information_theory) and [Coding theory](/Coding_theory)

Closely intertwined with [probability](/Probability) and [statistics](/Statistics), information theory quantifies information itself. [Claude Shannon](/Claude_Shannon) pioneered this field to establish fundamental limits on operations like data compression and reliable data storage and communication. &#91;60&#93;

Coding theory, on the other hand, examines the properties and applications of [codes](/Code)—systems for transforming information. These codes are crucial for [data compression](/Data_compression), [cryptography](/Cryptography), [error detection and correction](/Error_detection_and_correction), and increasingly, [network coding](/Network_coding). The goal is to design efficient and robust methods for [data transmission](/Data_transmission).

