##### Image and Sound Processing

*   Main article: [Data processing](/Data_processing)

Information, in its myriad forms—images, sound, video—is the raw material. Processing these [bits](/Bit) of information, often transmitted via [signals](/Signal), is central to informatics, the European perspective on computing. This field examines information processing algorithms irrespective of the carrier, be it electrical, mechanical, or biological. It plays a significant role in [information theory](/Information_theory), [telecommunications](/Telecommunications), and [information engineering](/Information_engineering), with applications ranging from [medical image computing](/Medical_image_computing) to [speech synthesis](/Speech_synthesis). A persistent question in theoretical computer science remains: what is the lower bound on the complexity of [fast Fourier transform](/Fast_Fourier_transform) algorithms? &#91;List of unsolved problems in computer science&#93;

