#### Computer Systems

##### Computer Architecture and Microarchitecture

*   Main articles: [Computer architecture](/Computer_architecture), [Microarchitecture](/Microarchitecture), and [Computer engineering](/Computer_engineering)

Computer architecture defines the conceptual design and fundamental operational structure of a computer system, with a focus on the internal workings of the central processing unit and memory access. &#91;65&#93; Computer engineers delve into [computational logic](/Computational_logic) and hardware design, from individual [processor](/Processor_(computing)) components and [microcontrollers](/Microcontroller) to entire [supercomputers](/Supercomputer) and [embedded systems](/Embedded_system). The term "architecture" in this context was notably used by Lyle R. Johnson and [Frederick P. Brooks Jr.](/Frederick_P._Brooks_Jr.) in 1959.

